Date:  0/0/1956
Source:  Wool Away!
Author:  BOWEN
Vol / Page:  155
Edition:
Quote:  BOOTLACE. A long thin strip of skin cut off a sheep, seen mostly on last side. It usually comes from wrinkled skin.
